OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FFor the BBC's supporters, the much
OL,7,Fanticipated green paper on its future
OL,8,Fmust have seemed like an early
OL,9,FChristmas present.
OL,11,FIgnore the headlines in some newspapers
OL,12,Fwhich aren't friends of the
OL,13,Fcorporation. This was a vote of
OL,14,Fconfidence in the BBC.
OL,16,FThe BBC is simply much too important to
OL,17,Fweaken and undermine. The green paper
OL,18,Frecognises this.
OL,20,FThe debate on what happens next should
OL,21,Fbe a positive one ` not an existential
OL,22,Fbattle.
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,200,140,120,200,0,100
PN,15902
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe points for discussion include
OL,7,Fgovernance arrangements, political
OL,8,Fappointees to the board and whether the
OL,9,Fcorporation should have an actual
OL,10,Frequirement to counter misinformation
OL,11,Felsewhere.
OL,13,FSupporters of the BBC should have no
OL,14,Fdifficulty entering into this
OL,15,Fdiscussion.
OL,17,FAny organisation which is to survive
OL,18,Fneeds to be self critical.
OL,20,FWhat can the BBC do better? Are there
OL,21,Fthings it does too little or too much
OL,22,Fof?
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,200,140,120,200,0,100
PN,15903
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FHow can major errors ` like the
OL,7,Fnotorious Donald Trump edit ` be dealt
OL,8,Fwith more effectively?
OL,10,FWhat the green paper is not suggesting
OL,11,Fis a smaller BBC or one which retreats
OL,12,Ffrom popular programmes.
OL,14,FIt should be no surprise that a green
OL,15,Fpaper from a Labour government is not
OL,16,Fpandering to philosophical or
OL,17,Fideological critics on the right `
OL,18,Fthose who would want the BBC
OL,19,Fprivatised, abolished or significantly
OL,20,Fsmaller in scale.
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,200,140,120,200,0,100
PN,15904
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FOne area for debate is funding. Are
OL,7,Fthere realistic alternatives to the
OL,8,Flicence fee?
OL,10,FNothing is off the table at this stage
OL,11,Fother than direct funding from general
OL,12,Ftaxation.
OL,14,FArguments about commercial funding and
OL,15,Fsubscription are being revisited. But
OL,16,Ffew within the industry think there is
OL,17,Fthe slightest chance of any existing TV
OL,18,For radio services carrying ads or going
OL,19,Fbehind a paywall.
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,200,140,120,200,0,100
PN,15905
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe realistic question is about whether
OL,7,Fthere is a way to address the genuine
OL,8,Fproblems with the current system.
OL,10,FInstead of a flat fee, is there a way
OL,11,Fto create some link with the ability of
OL,12,Fsomeone to pay? What about people who
OL,13,Fdon't have a TV (or access to iPlayer)
OL,14,Fbut who listen to BBC Radio or use the
OL,15,Frest of the website?
OL,17,FThe idea of a household charge `
OL,18,Flinked, perhaps, to council tax bands `
OL,19,Fhas attractions. But there needs to be
OL,20,Fa proper debate on pros and cons.
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,200,140,120,200,0,100
PN,15906
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FI actually would not be completely
OL,7,Fsurprised if the licence fee survives
OL,8,Fagain, perhaps with minor modifications
OL,9,For discounts for the poorest.
OL,11,FIn a way, it has only become a flat
OL,12,Frate fee over the past 30 years.
OL,14,FUntil the early 60s, those on the
OL,15,Flowest incomes may well not have had a
OL,16,FTV ` just a radio.
OL,18,FColour TVs were aspirational items for
OL,19,Fmuch of the 70s. Those on low incomes
OL,20,For with other priorities would have
OL,21,Fbeen likely to watch in black and
OL,22,Fwhite.
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,200,140,120,200,0,100
PN,15907
SC,0007
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F159A1773000680
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FEven today, the daily cost of the TV
OL,7,Flicence is a fraction of the cost of
OL,8,Fany major newspaper or a decent
OL,9,Ftakeaway coffee.
OL,11,FThose who care about the corporation `
OL,12,Fincluding critical friends and
OL,13,Fsupporters who see real failings `
OL,14,Fshould join the debate about the BBC's
OL,15,Ffuture.
OL,17,FBut those who are fundamentally opposed
OL,18,Fto its existence or compulsory funding
OL,19,Fby the public are unlikely to have the
OL,20,Fear of ministers.
OL,23,EPub: 16-Dec-2025Upppppppppppppppppppppp
